Assistant Secretary of State for Western Hemisphere Affairs, Brian A. Nichols, recently visited Haiti to demonstrate the United States' commitment to the country. He was accompanied by National Security Council Senior Director for the Western Hemisphere, Juan Gonzalez, and Deputy Assistant Secretary of State, Mark Wells. During their visit, the delegation met with representatives from Haitian civil society, including the Montana Group, and political stakeholders to express U.S. support for inclusive Haitian-led solutions that strengthen the country's institutions. They also met with Prime Minister Ariel Henry and Foreign Minister Claude Joseph to discuss the humane repatriation of migrants, the investigation into President Moise's assassination, and the need to improve the security situation in Haiti. The Biden-Harris Administration remains dedicated to supporting the Haitian people during this challenging time.